-- Mexico’s Peso Declines; Fixed-Rate Bond Yields Increase
-- B y   B e n   B a i n
-- 2012-08-09T12:49:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-09/mexico-s-peso-declines-fixed-rate-bond-yields-increase.html
Mexico ’s peso dropped 0.1 percent to
13.1595 per U.S. dollar at 7:43 a.m. in Mexico City.  The yield on Mexico’s peso bonds due in 2024 rose two basis
points, or 0.02 percentage point, to 5.5 percent, according to
prices compiled by Bloomberg. The price fell 0.24 centavo to
140.25 centavos per peso.  To contact the reporter on this story:
